726,IssuesEvent,2017-07-12 09:06:56+00:00,45852176,arose/nglview,1382074,jbarnoud,,,opened,ipywidgets should be required,[],[],0,"`ipywidgets` is declared as an extra requirement in `setup.py`, yet it is not possible to import nglview without it. It should therefore be a plain requirement.

```
import nglview

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
ModuleNotFoundError                       Traceback (most recent call last)
<ipython-input-1-f9b21067454f> in <module>()
      6 from matplotlib import pyplot
      7 
----> 8 import nglview

~/Envs/mda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/nglview/__init__.py in <module>()
     29 # interface
     30 from .config import BACKENDS
---> 31 from .widget import NGLWidget
     32 from .base_adaptor import *
     33 from .adaptor import *

~/Envs/mda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/nglview/widget.py in <module>()
      7 import numpy as np
      8 from IPython.display import display
----> 9 from ipywidgets import Box, DOMWidget, widget_image
     10 from traitlets import (Unicode, Bool, Dict, List, Int, Integer, observe,
     11                        CaselessStrEnum)

ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'ipywidgets'
```

Note that the installation instructions do mention that `ipywidget` is required.

- Version report

Tested on nglview 0.6.5. As of d74a8fca983ccfac81f411d3fa8531831f69640c, `setup.py` does not declare `ipywidgets` as a plain requirement.
",{},{}
747,IssuesEvent,2015-03-29 05:16:23+00:00,4689577,cjdrake/pyeda,1093960,cjdrake,,,opened,Invalid memory access,[],[],0,"This `picosat_reset` call attempts to free the PicoSAT instance after `state` has already been freed. Not sure why it doesn't fail harder, but it's an invalid memory access.

