933,IssuesEvent,2016-12-17 06:47:51+00:00,10865487,upbit/pixivpy,302680,upbit,,,closed,Encoding issue while fetching rank list,"[{'id': 44526568, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/upbit/pixivpy/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 44526570, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/upbit/pixivpy/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],2,"Hi, I've found that the json result of `ranking_all()` is bad encoding(at least in my environment), there may occurs things like:
```
  'tags': ['Fate/GrandOrder',
           'Fate',
           'ĺŁŤĺ\x89Ł',
           'ĺŁŤă\x81\x90ă\x81\xa0',
           'Fate/GO500usersĺ\x85Ľă\x82\x8a'],
```

And I also found that if I edit the code in `api.BasePixivAPI.requests_call()` to this:
```
    def requests_call(self, method, url, headers={}, params=None, data=None, stream=False):
        """""" requests http/https call for Pixiv API """"""
        try:
            if (method == 'GET'):
                r = requests.get(url, params=params, headers=headers, stream=stream, **self.requests_kwargs)
            elif (method == 'POST'):
                r = requests.post(url, params=params, data=data, headers=headers, stream=stream, **self.requests_kwargs)
            elif (method == 'DELETE'):
                r = requests.delete(url, params=params, data=data, headers=headers, stream=stream, **self.requests_kwargs)
            r.encoding = 'utf-8'  # Manually set the encoding
            return r
        except Exception as e:
            raise PixivError('requests %s %s error: %s' % (method, url, e))

        raise PixivError('Unknow method: %s' % method)
```
Everything will be fine.

I hope this helps you.",{},{}
