2152,IssuesEvent,2015-03-03 10:26:30+00:00,9289343,svinota/pyroute2,5222698,jtluka,,,opened,cannot call isinstance() with IPRSocket,[],[],0,"Hi,
LNST is incompatible with the 0.3.5 version of pyroute2 (available via pip). I've came up with the following simplified reproducer,

```
>>> from pyroute2 import IPRSocket
>>> s = IPRSocket()
>>> s.bind()
>>> isinstance(s, IPRSocket)
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""<stdin>"", line 1, in <module>
TypeError: isinstance() arg 2 must be a class, type, or tuple of classes and types
>>> IPRSocket
<functools.partial object at 0x7ffc4650e7e0>
>>> IPRSocket()
<pyroute2.netlink.rtnl.IPRSocket object at 0x7ffc3a2e5320>
>>> 
```

I know that this is because of introducing functools.partial code but do you have any idea, how can we fix this?",{},{}
