2413,IssuesEvent,2018-02-02 15:24:58+00:00,15408116,ergoithz/browsepy,1101062,kovalevfm,,,closed,Flask from_envvar reads only uppercase values,[],[],1,"http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/0.12/config/#configuring-from-files
> The configuration files themselves are actual Python files. Only values in uppercase are actually stored in the config object later on. So make sure to use uppercase letters for your config keys.

```python
app.config.update(
    directory_base=compat.getcwd(),
    directory_start=None,
...
if 'BROWSEPY_SETTINGS' in os.environ:
   app.config.from_envvar('BROWSEPY_SETTINGS')
```
Lowercase options like `directory_base` can't be read from configuration file passed with os env variable",{},{}
