4071,IssuesEvent,2018-07-18 08:35:18+00:00,70314805,kyuupichan/electrumx,3319176,kyuupichan,,,closed,Syncing on SBC with HDD is (too?) slow,[],[],4,"Hi, 

I would like to share my experience on syncing electurmx 1.4.3 on [ODROID-HC1](https://www.hardkernel.com/main/products/prdt_info.php?g_code=G150229074080) single board computer.

It has 2GB ram, and I have attached HGST HTS721075A9E630 HDD (7200RPM) that has Debian Stretch installed.

I have localy compiled Python 3.6.6, and had to choose `plyvel==0.9` because more recent version does not build on Stretch.

Current settings are:
```
# cat /etc/electrumx.conf
DAEMON_URL=http://XXX:YYY@127.0.0.1:8332/
TCP_PORT=50001
SSL_PORT=50002
HOST=0.0.0.0
SSL_CERTFILE=/etc/electrum/server.cert
SSL_KEYFILE=/etc/electrum/server.key
CACHE_MB=1024
```

Electrumx shares same SBC with bitcoind v0.16.1. _Bitcoind synced in two weeks_, thoug electrumx is currently running _for 41 days and counting_, with quite some ETA left:

```
journalctl -u electrumx
...
Jul 06 11:21:46 odroid-hc1 electrumx_server.py[18601]: INFO:BlockProcessor:our height: 512,347 daemon: 530,691 UTXOs 283MB hist 201MB
Jul 06 11:32:30 odroid-hc1 electrumx_server.py[18601]: INFO:BlockProcessor:our height: 512,357 daemon: 530,692 UTXOs 290MB hist 208MB
