CPU usage of `elecrtrumx` and `bitcoind` usually keeps below 10% (from total 800% as it's octa-core ARM).

Not sure what have I expected, really, but seems using HDD on low-ram system (with FS cache being too small and useless?) doesn't look practical. I am actually planing to upgrade Odroid to SSD at sime time in the future though.

Today, I could just sync on my SSD-powered laptop I guess, but I just wanted to try that on my SBC.

Is there anything that could be done to improve this, or it's just the reallity to be used to? :)

",{},{}
