4260,IssuesEvent,2017-07-13 19:15:17+00:00,16787349,workhorsy/py-cpuinfo,6730980,AkshatM,,,opened,Add support for retrieving L3 cache size if possible,[],[],0,"This limitation has been [referenced here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45088555/find-cpu-l3-cache-size-using-python). I would like to add this capability to `py-cpuinfo`.

It looks like the current technique in `py-cpuinfo` for retrieving L2 cache size info is to use the CPUID opcode with the extended L2 feature set. I've tried digging around for a way to use CPUID for L3 cache, as that would be the most compliant across different OSs, but no luck. 

For certain operating systems, L3 cache size is easily retrievable e.g. [`/proc/cpuinfo/` on Linux ](https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/113555/when-speaking-about-cache-size-of-a-cpu-we-only-need-the-size-of-the-cache-at-t) directly references the L3 cache, while [`WMIC CPU`](https://www.techvigil.com/tips-tricks/379/verify-processor-cache-size-speed/) can be used on Windows. 

If permissible, I would like to try adding support for Linux and Windows specifically while trying to find a processor-based solution (unless you are aware of one). Thoughts? ",{},{}
