4543,IssuesEvent,2016-11-30 05:24:56+00:00,45618882,mverleg/pyjson_tricks,12261158,rldotai,,,opened,Handle encoding for numpy array scalars,[],[],0,"The `json_tricks` library will serialize instances of `numpy.ndarray` but if you pass it an array scalar (e.g., a single element of an array, which have datatypes like `numpy.int64`, `numpy.float64`, etc.)

For example:

```python
>>> z = np.array([1,2,3])  
>>> json_tricks.dumps(z)
'{""dtype"": ""int64"", ""shape"": [3], ""__ndarray__"": [1, 2, 3]}'
>>> json_tricks.dumps(z[0])
