(b'\x80\x04\x95=\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x8c\x08datetime\x94\x8c\x08date' b'time\x94\x93\x94C\n\x07\xe1\x04\x0f\r1\x15\x08\x7f\xa8\x94\x8c\x04py' b'tz\x94\x8c\x04_UTC\x94\x93\x94)R\x94\x86\x94R\x94.')
```

I would rather expect showing the corresponding text representation of the object:

```
datetime.datetime(2017, 4, 15, 13, 35, 51, 169443, tzinfo=<UTC>)
```

Is it possible? Or am I doing something wrong?

Environment:

```
$ pip freeze|grep redis
django-redis==4.7.0
django-redisboard==3.0.2
redis==2.10.5

$ pip freeze|grep Django
Django==1.11

$ python --version
Python 3.5.2
```
",{},{}
