5873,IssuesEvent,2018-04-27 16:20:24+00:00,13226530,alanjds/drf-nested-routers,1211530,Hooksie,,,opened,NestedRouters should inherit trailing_slash from their parent,[],[],0,"When setting a nested router as the child of a parent, one could reasonably expect the trailing slash behavior to be the same as the parent (allowing a single point to define the setting). Currently, `drf-nested-routers` does not do this; `trailing_slash=False` must be set for every child router when trailing slashes are not desired.

Current behavior:

```
from rest_framework_nested import routers

root_router = routers.DefaultRouter(trailing_slash=False)
root_router.register('a', SomeViewSet, basename='a')
nested_router = routers.NestedDefaultRouter(root_router, 'a', lookup='xyz')
nested_router.register('b', JobTargetViewSet, base_name='b')

> root_router.urls
[<URLPattern '^a$' [name='a-list']>,
 <URLPattern '^a\.(?P<format>[a-z0-9]+)/?$' [name='a-list']>,
 <URLPattern '^a/(?P<pk>[^/.]+)$' [name='a-detail']>,
 <URLPattern '^a/(?P<pk>[^/.]+)\.(?P<format>[a-z0-9]+)/?$' [name='a-detail']>]

> nested_router.urls
[<URLPattern '^a/(?P<xyz_pk>[^/.]+)/b/$' [name='b-list']>,
 <URLPattern '^a/(?P<xyz_pk>[^/.]+)/b\.(?P<format>[a-z0-9]+)/?$' [name='b-list']>,
 <URLPattern '^a/(?P<xyz_pk>[^/.]+)/b/(?P<pk>[^/.]+)/$' [name='b-detail']>,
 <URLPattern '^a/(?P<xyz_pk>[^/.]+)/b/(?P<pk>[^/.]+)\.(?P<format>[a-z0-9]+)/?$' [name='b-detail']>]
```
note the trailing slashes in `nested_router.urls` patterns.

The desired behavior would be no trailing slashes on the `nested_router.urls` patterns. This behavior can currently be gotten by setting `trailing_slash=False` explicitly on all nested routers.

This seems simple enough to change by inspecting `parent_router` during `NestedMixin.__init__` if trailing_slash unspecified or `None`. 

I can write this if there is interest, it should be pretty trivial.",{},{}
