6346,IssuesEvent,2018-01-19 12:29:21+00:00,5525736,ColinDuquesnoy/QDarkStyleSheet,5084939,dpizetta,,,opened,Option to choose Qt API from environment variable,[],[],0,"Hi, I've been using QtPy and the way to choose the Qt API is great. I think you can use it in your project.

```
def load_stylesheet_from_qt_api():
    """"""Load stylesheet from Qt API environment variable.""""""

    # get qt api from environment variable
    qt_api = os.environ['QT_API']

    if qt_api == 'pyqt5':
        return qdarkstyle.load_stylesheet_pyqt5()
    elif qt_api == 'pyqt':
        return qdarkstyle.load_stylesheet(pyside=False)
    elif qt_api == 'pyside':
        return qdarkstyle.load_stylesheet()
    elif qt_api == 'pyside2':
        raise NotImplementedError(""PySide 2 is not supported yet."")
    else:
        raise ImportError(""QT_API not defined, please set it using one of these ['pyqt5', 'pyqt', 'pyside2', 'pyside']."")
```
I can implement if you approve :)
",{},{}
6353,IssuesEvent,2015-03-12 01:19:23+00:00,1576129,KristianOellegaard/django-hvad,120373,gone,,,opened,Proxy models and admin list_display don't seem to work togeter,[],[],0,"I have a situation like this:

