6355,IssuesEvent,2015-02-17 16:42:13+00:00,1576129,KristianOellegaard/django-hvad,754333,sephii,,,opened,Support for multi-table inheritance,[],[],0,"I couldn't find anything in the docs so I don't know what's the supposed status of this, but from what I experienced, multi-table inheritance doesn't work. Suppose you have the following model:

```python
class BaseBook(TranslatableModel):
    translations = TranslatedFields(
        name=models.CharField(max_length=100)
    )

class Book(BaseBook):
    chapters = models.IntegerField()
```

Hvad will complain:
```
django.core.exceptions.ImproperlyConfigured: No TranslatedFields found on <class 'demo.models.Book'>, subclasses of TranslatableModel must define TranslatedFields.
```

And if you define `TranslatedFields`, you then get an error:
```
