6485,IssuesEvent,2017-11-13 17:48:31+00:00,26947860,facelessuser/pymdown-extensions,1055125,facelessuser,,,opened,Mention link shortening,"[{'id': 151820353, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/facelessuser/pymdown-extensions/labels/Feature', 'name': 'Feature', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}, {'id': 151745391, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/facelessuser/pymdown-extensions/labels/Maybe', 'name': 'Maybe', 'color': 'bfd4f2', 'default': False}]",[],0,"MagicLink has the ability to shrink repository links for commits, issues, and pulls to a short hand form for display, but currently has omitted doing the same for mentions.

GitHub, GitLab, and Bitbucket all do user links in the form `https://url.com/user`.  This is easy enough to detect and shorten to something like `<a href=""https://url.com/user"">@user</a>`, but the problem is that not every link in this form is a user: `https://github.com/marketplace`.

So if we want to shorten the url, we might need something like user name blacklist since we are not utilizing the GitHub, GitLab, or Bitbucket API to verify user names, nor is that planned.  We could provide general blacklist, and if a user needs to reference a link that is not in the blacklist, maybe the user could temporarily append a user blacklist until a pull can be made to update the main blacklist.

This is just an idea for the possibility of supporting this. The other alternative is to just not support this.",{},{}
