7373,IssuesEvent,2018-01-29 11:29:13+00:00,1977148,plone/plone.app.multilingual,36721,iham,72034,plone,opened,single language does not create a lrf,"[{'id': 35334181, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/plone/plone.app.multilingual/labels/01%20type:%20bug', 'name': '01 type: bug', 'color': 'fa0000', 'default': False}, {'id': 274228401, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/plone/plone.app.multilingual/labels/05%20type:%20question', 'name': '05 type: question', 'color': 'fa00fa', 'default': False}]",[],0,"as the title tells: why is that not happening?

i wanted to create a single language to be prepared for further upcoming languages which might be added later AND to have a root folder to restrict addable contenttypes.

when setting two languages are set, the pam creates those two folders are created. when i then remove one language the corresponding folder is deleted and the second lrf is not. so having only one lrf is basically possible, but a bit hacky to do it that way.

allowing a single language also to create a lrf would be good.",{},{}
7379,IssuesEvent,2015-09-09 07:55:23+00:00,2432511,plone/plone.app.linkintegrity,453208,pbauer,72034,plone,closed,Linkintegrity-Relations not created when creating new objects,[],[],2,"Steps to reproduce:

1. create page1
2. create page2 and (during creation) add a link in the richtext-field to page1
3. delete page1: no LinkIntegrityNotificationException will be fired

If you edit page2 again (before deleting page1) a LinkIntegrityNotificationException will be fired

So far we tried replacing the subscriber with the following:
```xml
<subscriber
    for=""Products.CMFCore.interfaces._content.IContentish
         zope.lifecycleevent.interfaces.IObjectAddedEvent""
    handler=""..handlers.addedDexterity"" />
```
```python
def addedDexterity(obj, event):
    from plone.app.referenceablebehavior.referenceable import IReferenceable as IRef
    if IRef.providedBy(obj):
        modifiedDexterity(obj, None)
```
Upon inspecting page1 after step 2. we can see that it has no backrelation:
```python
>>> from Products.Archetypes.interfaces.referenceable import IReferenceable
>>> IReferenceable(obj).getBackReferences()
[None]
```
it should be:
```python
>>> IReferenceable(obj).getBackReferences()
[<Document at /Plone/page2>]
```
We will probably have more time investigate further later today.",{},{}
7410,IssuesEvent,2017-05-09 18:57:53+00:00,18780981,cloudera/impyla,50748,JoshRosen,87383,cloudera,opened,KeyError: 'NULL' when querying Spark ThriftServer where a result column has NULL type ,[],[],0,"I am using `impyla` to query Spark's Hive ThriftServer using a query roughly like the following:

```
SELECT MIN(NULL) OVER () AS int_col from table_1 t1
```

This results in the following stacktrace inside of `impyla`:

```
  File ""/Users/joshrosen/anaconda/lib/python2.7/site-packages/impala/hiveserver2.py"", line 393, in fetchmany
    local_buffer.append(next(self))
  File ""/Users/joshrosen/anaconda/lib/python2.7/site-packages/impala/hiveserver2.py"", line 437, in next
    return self.__next__()
  File ""/Users/joshrosen/anaconda/lib/python2.7/site-packages/impala/hiveserver2.py"", line 450, in __next__
    self.buffersize)
  File ""/Users/joshrosen/anaconda/lib/python2.7/site-packages/impala/hiveserver2.py"", line 1047, in fetch
    convert_types=convert_types)
  File ""/Users/joshrosen/anaconda/lib/python2.7/site-packages/impala/hiveserver2.py"", line 1052, in _wrap_results
    return CBatch(results, schema, convert_types=convert_types)
  File ""/Users/joshrosen/anaconda/lib/python2.7/site-packages/impala/hiveserver2.py"", line 730, in __init__
    for (i, col) in enumerate(trowset.columns)]
KeyError: 'NULL'
```

I think the right fix here is to add an entry for `NULL` to _TTypeId_to_TColumnValue_getters. The Thrift `NULL_TYPE` id is already handled elsewhere in this codebase in `_thrift_gen` `ttypes.py` in the `_VALUES_TO_NAMES` map.",{},{}
7422,IssuesEvent,2018-08-20 14:27:48+00:00,788264,zeromq/pyzmq,151929,minrk,109777,zeromq,closed,TypeError when sending bytebuffer using PyPy-3.5.3 v6.0.0,[],[],1,"Hi,
I am unable to send a bytebuffer from a PUSH socket using pypy3.
The code was ran using `virtualenv -p pypy3`, and a [pypy3 linux x86-64 prebuilt binary](https://www.pypy.org/download.html).

