PyPy-3.5.3 (fdd60ed87e94, Apr 24 2018, 06:10:04)
[PyPy 6.0.0 with GCC 6.2.0 20160901]
```
Here is my system info :
(Note that Running this code from the [pypy3-6.0.0 image](https://hub.docker.com/_/pypy/) yields the same issue.)
```
Distributor ID:	Ubuntu
Description:	Ubuntu 18.04.1 LTS
Release:	18.04
Codename:	bionic
```
Here is the a minimum amount of code to reproduce this issue :

```python3
#!/usr/bin/env pypy3

# filename : push.py

import zmq

ctx = zmq.Context()
push = ctx.socket(zmq.PUSH)
push.bind(""tcp://*:3001"")

buf = bytearray(b'\x00')

push.send(buf)
```

