8227,IssuesEvent,2018-03-23 13:29:21+00:00,123314988,abusix/ahocorapy,483596,FrederikP,404185,abusix,closed,Not all words are matched,[],[],4,"Hi,

Thanks for this pure python implementation which performs really awesome under pypy.

However we found out that under some circumstances not all words are matched, consider the following example:

```python
text = '/foo/bar'
words = ['/bar', '/foo/bar', 'bar']
tree = KeywordTree(case_insensitive=True)
for word in words:
    tree.add(word)
tree.finalize()
print set([word for word, position in tree.search_all(text)])  # set(['/foo/bar', '/bar'])
```

The expected result would be ``set(['/foo/bar', '/bar', 'bar'])`` but we got only ``set(['/foo/bar', '/bar'])``",{},{}
