8696,IssuesEvent,2018-01-23 16:42:07+00:00,79510167,pypa/pipenv,119893,kennethreitz,647025,pypa,closed,Is there a way to install to custom-packages in Pipfile?,[],[],2,"My understanding is that Pipfile supports the ability to install many categories of packages with the default being `[packages]` and `[dev-packages]`. Is there a way using pipenv to install to a custom group and install all of the packages under a custom group?

Example implementation if this is not already implemented could be:

`pipenv install requests --custom test` to install the requests package under `[test-packages]`
`pipenv install --custom test` to install all packages under `[test-packages]`
