8754,IssuesEvent,2017-11-03 14:00:25+00:00,1446474,pypa/virtualenv,23497517,cryvate,647025,pypa,opened,Add --extra-packages to support installing packages with pip after creation,[],[],0,"To bootstrap an environment and create consistency within a project, company, ... it can be useful to make sure any environment created has some basic packages for consistency and easy of use. This could be for:

  * using a replacement for setuptools [(PEP518 suggests this should be made easy)](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0518/)
  * some basic numeric packages (numpy, pandas, ipython) for those who are mainly doing data analysis
  * install package such that the right version is used, or it is available (woes related to PEP518, in particular numpy and packages that depend on it)
  * reduce complexity of bootstrapping tools. If only an install of packages with certain parameters

An environment variable can be used automatically (VIRTUALENV_EXTRA_PACKAGES), easily set by sys admins, with user being able to overwrite it or use the command line.

The implementation is as simple as adding:

     parser.add_option(
        '--extra-packages',
        dest='extra_packages',
        action='store',
        help=""Passed to 'pip install' in new virtual environment after creation."")

when creating the parser [(e.g. here)](https://github.com/pypa/virtualenv/blob/e5922654e10c4c5494241112a3645079db186222/virtualenv.py#L644) and

    if options.extra_packages:
        extra_packages = options.extra_packages.split(',')
        logger.start_progress(""Installing (with pip install) %s..."" % ', '.join(extra_packages))

        cmd = [join(home_dir, 'bin', 'pip'), 'install'] + extra_packages

        logger.indent += 2
        try:
            call_subprocess(cmd, show_stdout=False, stdin='')
        finally:
            logger.indent -= 2
            logger.end_progress()

[in between `create_environment` and `after_install`.](https://github.com/pypa/virtualenv/blob/e5922654e10c4c5494241112a3645079db186222/virtualenv.py#L713)

I will create a PR later and link it.",{},{}
