9086,IssuesEvent,2017-08-13 09:58:09+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,492549,jni,897180,scikit-image,opened,Consider using/vendoring @astrofrog's fast-histogram,[],[],0,"A **lot** of functions in skimage use image histograms for various purposes (e.g. histeq, or thresholding), so I think as a whole, optimising our histogram computation could result in a significant speedup for the library. @astrofrog recently released fast-histogram, a library for fast 1D and 2D histogram computation (see https://github.com/astrofrog/fast-histogram). It's available on PyPI, so we could either pick it up as a lightweight dependency, or vendor it.

Please read @astrofrog's FAQ before suggesting that this should be added to NumPy. ;)",{},{}
