9199,IssuesEvent,2015-10-06 16:43:49+00:00,9252533,numenta/nupic,15566,rhyolight,1039191,numenta,reopened,"remove duplicit Numpy dependency, already in nupic.bindings","[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/duplicate', 'name': 'duplicate', 'color': 'cccccc'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/type:build', 'name': 'type:build', 'color': '006b75'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/type:cleanup', 'name': 'type:cleanup', 'color': '006b75'}]",[],2,"`numpy` is a core dependency of nupic, but it's already included in `nupic.bindings` and therefor should not be defined in nupic again. 

The problems with this were reported by @rhyolight when installation went twice through installing numpy, as different versions were required for core(bindings) and nupic. 

The removal speeds up time for installation and could avoid some tricky problems when different version is used for compilation and then for runtime. 

",{},{}
