9276,IssuesEvent,2016-02-17 17:00:44+00:00,30921526,mozilla-services/cliquet,546692,leplatrem,1066228,mozilla-services,closed,moving to enum.Enum,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla-services/cliquet/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla-services/cliquet/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c'}]",[],3,"We have an ad-hoc Enum class at https://github.com/mozilla-services/cliquet/blob/master/cliquet/utils.py#L152

it behaves very differently from Python 3.4 Enum - https://docs.python.org/3/library/enum.html and even makes our Project shadow the stdlib Enum in 3.4

I don't see any good reason to keep ours, as we can use ""enum34"" which backports enum in all Python version.

However, that's not a small change - so I'd like to ask here before doing it - in case I am missing a good reason to keep it

",{},{}
