9583,IssuesEvent,2016-10-22 18:34:35+00:00,3314548,eea/eea.facetednavigation,34800,david-batranu,1176627,eea,closed,Batch not working on Plone 5,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/eea/eea.facetednavigation/labels/Plone%205', 'name': 'Plone 5', 'color': '1d76db'}]","[{'login': 'david-batranu', 'id': 34800, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/34800?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/david-batranu', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/david-batranu', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/david-batranu/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/david-batranu/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/david-batranu/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/david-batranu/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/david-batranu/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/david-batranu/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/david-batranu/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/david-batranu/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/david-batranu/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"When you click on a page in batch navigation, you always get the first page.
The problem is that the request url is:
@@faceted_query?b_start%5B%5D=40&version=0efb47f17f1f466fcada64f5f7925879
there is a [] just after the b_start parameter.
I've found that this is coming from that part of the view.js javascript

`  get: function(){
    var hash = jQuery.bbq.getState();
    console.debug(hash);
    var query = {};
    var types = [""number"", ""boolean"", ""string""];
    jQuery.each(hash, function(key, value){
      var value_type = typeof(value);
      if(jQuery.inArray(value_type, types) !== -1){
        value = [value];
      }
      query[key] = value;
    });
    return query;
  },
`
The following lines:
      if(jQuery.inArray(value_type, types) !== -1){
        value = [value];
      }
adds the [ ] around the value which is bad with b_start. I don't really understand the aim of doing that.

If you comment those three lines, the batching work as expected.",{},{}
