10845,IssuesEvent,2016-01-06 03:34:26+00:00,37935815,bxlab/bx-python,1299177,ghuls,2084107,bxlab,opened,Reimport bx-python from mercurial to git with hg-fast-export to fix broken commit difference,[],[],0," * I reimported bx-python from mercurial with hg-fast-export: https://bitbucket.org/james_taylor/bx-python/
 * Merged pull request #8 from bitbucket: https://bitbucket.org/james_taylor/bx-python/pull-requests/8/replace-outdated-distribute-with/diff
 * Readded 2 patches only available in your current git (one patch reworked as most of it was covered by pull request #8): https://github.com/bxlab/bx-python

https://github.com/ghuls/bx-python-fixed-history/

The reason I did it is because there is something wrong in the git history:

Commit 7419905c7af63d039ef108a79acae9be872c02c0 changes way to many files:
```
$ git log --stat
commit 7419905c7af63d039ef108a79acae9be872c02c0
Author: Brent Pedersen <bpederse@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 10 12:14:02 2015 -0600

    The bigwig/bigbed stuff is slow. This commit improves the speed by about 2-fold.
    It is still slow, but more improvements would require larger design changes.
    
    Previously, where chunks of data were read as, for example:
    
       read_uint32()
       read_uint32()
       read_uint32()
    
    this changes that to read all 3 values in a single pass.
    
    I also removed some dead code.
    
    See: https://gist.github.com/brentp/c9b24554cff4bab0a0bc
    for the test of validity and the timing. The md5sums before
    and after for a whole-genome bigwig and bigbed are identical.
    
