In my version it looks much saner:
https://github.com/ghuls/bx-python-fixed-history/commit/378b2a0fc3667b386631de92cf5b1117b2250237

```
$ git log --stat
commit e9233394a78d1eb25b89f740ad7dd7628be29d35
Author: Brent Pedersen <bpederse@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 10 12:14:02 2015 -0600

    The bigwig/bigbed stuff is slow. This commit improves the speed by about 2-fold.
    It is still slow, but more improvements would require larger design changes.
    
    Previously, where chunks of data were read as, for example:
    
       read_uint32()
       read_uint32()
       read_uint32()
    
    this changes that to read all 3 values in a single pass.
    
    I also removed some dead code.
    
    See: https://gist.github.com/brentp/c9b24554cff4bab0a0bc
    for the test of validity and the timing. The md5sums before
    and after for a whole-genome bigwig and bigbed are identical.
    
    Output looks like:
    
    
    before bb: 10.4 seconds
    before bb: d2424d770247e721b43c2729cbe160a0
    before bw: 8.6 seconds
    before bw: 8529aaef661eb479c2bfe6e1ee4107db
    
    bb: d2424d770247e721b43c2729cbe160a0
    bb: 6.50828194618
    bw: 8529aaef661eb479c2bfe6e1ee4107db
    bw: 4.26337003708

 lib/bx/align/epo_tests.pyc |   Bin 11861 -> 0 bytes
 lib/bx/bbi/bbi_file.c      | 11164 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--------------------------------------------------
 lib/bx/bbi/bbi_file.pyx    |    94 +-
 lib/bx/bbi/bigbed_file.c   |  7069 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------------------------------
 lib/bx/bbi/bigbed_file.pyx |    44 +-
 lib/bx/bbi/bigwig_file.c   |  9374 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------------------------------------------
 lib/bx/bbi/bigwig_file.pyx |    60 +-
 7 files changed, 14879 insertions(+), 12926 deletions(-)
```

To fix your git repository:

``` bash
git clone https://github.com/ghuls/bx-python-fixed-history/
cd bx-python-fixed-history

git remote add bxlab https://github.com/bxlab/bx-python
git push -f bxlab master
```
Afterwards you can clone your repostitory again from git hub:
``` bash
cd .<right_directory>
git clone https://github.com/bxlab/bx-python
```",{},{}
10848,IssuesEvent,2016-08-19 23:22:14+00:00,58659170,bxlab/bx-python,1569186,lzamparo,2084107,bxlab,opened,Python 3.5 not supported for conda installs,[],[],0,"For a linux-64 python 3.5.1 environment, the conda install instructions fail:

 `[zamparol@machine]$ python --version
Python 3.5.1 :: Anaconda 2.4.1 (64-bit)`

`[zamparol@machine]$ conda --version
conda 4.1.11`

> [zamparol@machine]$ conda install -c bioconda bx-python
> Fetching package metadata .........
> Solving package specifications: ....
> 
> The following specifications were found to be in conflict:
>   - bx-python
>   - python 3.5*
> Use ""conda info <package>"" to see the dependencies for each package.

