10935,IssuesEvent,2017-05-05 17:31:44+00:00,81612762,trailofbits/manticore,2467355,mossberg,2314423,trailofbits,closed,Formalize API for adding constraints to State,"[{'id': 592708766, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/trailofbits/manticore/labels/api', 'name': 'api', 'color': 'd93f0b', 'default': False}]",[],4,"Currently, we informally have a `State.add` API that is used internally for adding constraints onto a State. It can incidentally be used as a public API, but this was never decided deliberately, so I think we should take some time to actually think if there's anything that should be improved.

imo, it's good except, should be renamed to `State.constrain`.",{},{}
10939,IssuesEvent,2017-10-20 14:51:31+00:00,81612762,trailofbits/manticore,18771,yan,2314423,trailofbits,closed,cannot import evm module ,"[{'id': 723733286, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/trailofbits/manticore/labels/ethereum', 'name': 'ethereum', 'color': 'e27af4', 'default': False}]",[],1,"### OS / Environment
Ubuntu 16.04 LTS

### Manticore version
0.1.4

### Python version
2.7 (virtualenv contained environment)


### Dependencies
boto==2.48.0
capstone==3.0.5rc2
manticore==0.1.4
ply==3.10
pyelftools==0.24
pysha3==1.0.2
unicorn==1.0.1
z3-solver==4.5.1.0.post2

### Summary of the problem
1.  When trying to run `example/evm` python files, following error was raised:
```shell 
 from manticore.platforms import evm
ImportError: cannot import name evm
```
This is due to in `evm\seth.py` line 4 was trying to import a python file named `evm.py`, but there is no class or module called evm inside any files, similarly on line5, `from manticore.platforms.evm import pck_msb` would throw a `module not found` error 

2. Another minor issue, is in the README.md, 
when i tried to install by running `python setup.py install`, all dependencies were added as expected, but the command `manticore *fileName*`would still throw `Z3NotFound` error, which is caused by no Z3 command under /bin. I solved it by running `sudo pip install z3-solver` which add z3 to my `usr/local/bin/z3` (without sudo, it doesn't work) 

Not sure this minor error was only because of my wrong-operation or missing steps during installation, but just to raise out for your knowledge. 

Thanks!
",{},{}
