11149,IssuesEvent,2016-06-27 15:06:09+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python,192456,daspecster,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,closed,[Documentation Issue] Anchor links have the text hidden underneath the top banner.,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/docs', 'name': 'docs', 'color': '0052cc'}]",[],1,"Page Name: all of them
Release: 0.16.0

Clicking an anchor link makes the text jump to the top (good), but then it's hidden by the top banner (bad).

This is especially a problem for small methods like [ColumnFamily.create()](https://googlecloudplatform.github.io/gcloud-python/stable/bigtable-column-family.html#gcloud.bigtable.column_family.ColumnFamily.create).

This is in the Chrome web browser, but I imagine the other browsers have this same problem. My recommendation would to remove the ""fixed"" positioning of the banner. It should not cover the text.",{},{}
11194,IssuesEvent,2015-03-10 05:50:27+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python,2389518,rstuart85,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,What's the feasibility of something like GridFS (from mongo) for entities greater then 1MB?,[],[],0,"MongoDB has implemented a feature called [GridFS](http://docs.mongodb.org/manual/core/gridfs/) for all of their drivers. It overcomes the 16MB BSON-document size limit. The Python code is [here](https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-python-driver/tree/master/gridfs).

The 1MB limit on entities can be an issue in some applications and a feature like GridFS would be a great way to overcome that. Is such a feature something that could live in this project?",{},{}
