11628,IssuesEvent,2016-07-20 19:39:46+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,compile.zinc should reify the `-encoding` flags,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/jvm-compile', 'name': 'jvm-compile', 'color': '0052cc'}]",[],0,"scalac and javac independently accept an `-encoding` flag to set the encoding for compilation. A properly configured repo will thus always set both:
```
[compile.zinc]
jvm_options: [
args: [
    '-S-encoding', '-SUTF-8',
    '-C-encoding', '-SUTF-8',
  ]
```

We should reify this into a compile.zinc setting. Unfortunately, rolling it out will be... interesting.",{},{}
11632,IssuesEvent,2017-12-05 00:46:58+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,7378,baroquebobcat,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,pytest-prep shouldn't do work when no python tests are in scope,[],[],0,"PytestPrep always creates a pytest binary, even when no pytest tests are in scope. PytestPrep also hits the network when it does resolution for the binary, and that binary isn't included in a buildcache entry.
If resolution fails, because the host isn't available or for some other reason, then the pants will fail even if no pytest tests were involved.",{},{}
