12169,IssuesEvent,2016-02-17 12:44:51+00:00,11003251,acorg/dark-matter,132978,terrycojones,4853692,acorg,closed,Make dark.reads.Reads accept an initial iterator containing reads,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/acorg/dark-matter/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],0,"The `filter` method of `dark.reads.Reads` returns a generator. If you want to filter some reads and make another `Reads` instance, you need to do something like:
```python
original = FastaReads(filename)
new = Reads()
for read in original.filter(...):
    new.add(read)
```
(or `list(map(new.add, original.filter(...)))`)

It would be nicer to say
```python
original = FastaReads(filename)
new = Reads(original.filter(...))
```

This is easy, we just add an optional iterable to the `__init__` of `Reads` and have it call `self.add` on the items in the argument.
",{},{}
