12259,IssuesEvent,2015-05-26 18:41:19+00:00,12407457,Exa-Networks/exabgp,136956,CrackerJackMack,5339170,Exa-Networks,opened,Regression is updates between 3.4.9 and 3.4.10,[],[],0,"Been running exabgp for a few months and noticed a regression when I updated to 3.4.10.  Looks like it might be an encoding issue related to asn4 ?  Meant to file this a while back but  just getting around to it :calendar: has been swamped.  Downgrading back to 3.4.9 fixed my issue for the time being and holding off on upgrading.  This is taken from my production systems so I don't have any packet dumps available for you but will try to provide enough information to recreate in the lab.

Partially sanitized.

Router
--------
``` 
System Mode: XMR
Chassis: NetIron 16-slot
```

Router config (SOP)
-----------------
```
route-map deny-all deny 10
!
!
ip prefix-list something-anycast-ipv4-range seq 5 permit 10.255.0.49/32
ip as-path access-list something-anycast-asn seq 5 permit _64902_
!
route-map  something-anycast-ipv4-in permit 10
    match ip address prefix-list something-anycast-ipv4-range
    match as-path something-anycast-asn
    set metric 0
!
router bgp
    neighbor SOMETHING-ANYCAST-IPV4 peer-group
    neighbor SOMETHING-ANYCAST-IPV4 remote-as 64902
    neighbor SOMETHING-ANYCAST-IPV4 remove-private-as
    neighbor SOMETHING-ANYCAST-IPV4 description ""INTERNAL something anycast""
    neighbor SOMETHING-ANYCAST-IPV4 password $BGP_MD5PASSWORD
    neighbor $EBGP_IPV4_NEIGHBOR peer-group SOMETHING-ANYCAST-IPV4
    address-family ipv4 unicast
        neighbor SOMETHING-ANYCAST-IPV4 route-map in  something-anycast-ipv4-in
        neighbor SOMETHING-ANYCAST-IPV4 route-map out deny-all
        neighbor SOMETHING-ANYCAST-IPV4 activate
    exit-address-family
exit
!
```

Exabgp config (for both 3.4.9 and 3.4.10)
-----------------------------------------------------

```bind
group something {
    description ""something"";
    router-id 10.252.79.4;

    local-address 10.252.79.4;
    local-as 64902;
    peer-as 65000;
    md5 ""xxx45xxxx"";

    family {
        ipv4 unicast;
    }

    neighbor 10.252.79.2 {
    }

    neighbor 10.252.79.3 {
    }

    process watch-something {
        encoder text;
        run ""/usr/local/bin/something_health.sh"";
    }
}
```

something_health.sh
---------------------------
```bash
#!/bin/bash
anycast=10.255.0.49
# stripped all healthcheck code and 
echo ""announce route $anycast next-hop self""
```

