riptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/injaleea/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/injaleea/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/injaleea/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/injaleea/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",3,"`tox -e system_tests` creates:

* junit-dmm-system_tests.xml
* junit-fgen-system_tests.xml
* junit-modinst-system_tests.xml
* junit-nidcpower-system_tests.xml
* junit-scope-system_tests.xml
* junit-switch-system_tests.xml

`tox -e  nidmm_system_tests` produces `nidmm_system_test_result.json` and so forth.

make clean doesn't get rid of these files.

At least we have a .gitignore entry for the XML files but not for the json files.

Adding build products to / is sloppy.

I think this should all go inside `bin/`, maybe under `bin/junit/` and `bin/kibana/` _if we can_ (I understand there are clients for this files).

If _we cannot_ then we should at least make sure they are all in .gitignore and cleaned up during make clean.
",{},{}
