12815,IssuesEvent,2017-07-06 01:20:52+00:00,71996613,blue-yonder/tsfresh,5770525,wsjzha,6234170,blue-yonder,opened,How is time in DataFrame used in feature extraction?,[],[],0,"Hello, I am new to time series feature extraction. I have two questions here:

1. why we need to have time in the DataFrame? I think it could be useful when the sampling frequency varies over time. However, if we have a time series data which is sampled at a fixed frequency, how does time help for feature extraction?

2. in some cases, how should I define time? Say I want to classify multiple events and I have multiple recording segments each event.  Here, I know the interval between two adjacent samples are the same but don't know the starting time for each segment. Also, the sequence of the samples has some useful information, but the starting time for each segment is not so useful. 

Thanks for any help!

",{},{}
