14511,IssuesEvent,2017-04-11 05:56:03+00:00,45062555,F5Networks/f5-common-python,18006037,wojtek0806,8935905,F5Networks,closed,required create parameter checking needs enchancement,[],"[{'login': 'wojtek0806', 'id': 18006037, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/18006037?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wojtek0806', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/wojtek0806', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wojtek0806/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wojtek0806/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wojtek0806/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wojtek0806/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wojtek0806/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wojtek0806/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wojtek0806/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wojtek0806/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wojtek0806/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"Currently create parameter checking does not include scenarios where we have 1 of x mandatory parameters required, this leads to unnecessary duplication when overloading create() methods in the resources. 

The required method __minimum_one_is_missing is already in the resources.py, just _create() needs a bit of refactoring to include that check.

We would also need to add another _meta_data entry to keep a record of those parameters for each resource. By default this should be empty set().",{},{}
