14534,IssuesEvent,2015-09-28 18:01:16+00:00,1151051,django-oscar/django-oscar,2071543,john-parton,9057806,django-oscar,opened,Child not included in Range when parent's product_class is included,[],[],0,"Basically, the `AbstractRange.contains_product` checks to see if `product.product_class_id` is in `self._class_ids()` but `product_class_id` is always `None` for child products.

