14900,IssuesEvent,2017-07-21 13:08:23+00:00,43816051,common-workflow-language/cwltool,1330696,mr-c,9947495,common-workflow-language,closed,ResourceRequirement file size error,[],[],0,"Thanks @mr-c for the kind assistance running this through BOSC 2017's Codefest.

## Expected Behavior

When running a workflow where we want to determine i.e input file sizes to estimate/predict system resources, cwltool nor cwltoil are able to provide those in runtime in the current implementation and specification.

## Actual Behavior

The workflow cannot determine the file size in runtime, required to implement dynamic resource requirements.

## Workflow Code

```
#!/usr/bin/env cwl-runner
class: CommandLineTool
cwlVersion: v1.0

requirements:
  ResourceRequirement:
      coresMin: $(inputs.special_file.size)
      coresMax: $(inputs.special_file.size)

inputs:
  special_file: File

outputs:
  output:
    type: stdout

baseCommand: echo

stdout: cores.txt

arguments: [ $(runtime.cores) ]
```

And the `-job` looks like this:

```
special_file:
  class: File
  path: special_file
```


