15117,IssuesEvent,2015-11-05 04:58:03+00:00,14284859,marshmallow-code/marshmallow,2379650,sloria,10334301,marshmallow-code,closed,`prefix` not respected when `dump_to` is set,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/marshmallow-code/marshmallow/labels/ready%20to%20claim', 'name': 'ready to claim', 'color': '009800'}]",[],1,"Applies only to the latest `dev` version.

From https://github.com/marshmallow-code/marshmallow/pull/311#issuecomment-152202176:

> So here's an issue that I just noticed.
> https://github.com/marshmallow-code/marshmallow/blob/dev/marshmallow/marshalling.py#L134
> 
> if field_obj.dump_to:
> key = field_obj.dump_to
> elif not self.prefix:
> key = attr_name
> else:
> key = ''"".join([self.prefix, attr_name])
> 
> What if there's a case where field_obj.dump_to is set AND self.prefix is set. Then, do we want key = ''.join([self.prefix, field_obj.dump_to])?
> 
> so maybe:
> 
> key = """" if not self.prefix else self.prefix
> if field_obj.dump_to:
> key += field_obj.dump_to
> else:
> key += attr_name
> 
> What do you think?
> @sloria @franciscod


",{},{}
15164,IssuesEvent,2018-07-01 12:33:19+00:00,112676803,apple/turicreate,11426676,igiloh,10639145,apple,opened,Improve unit tests - GPU tests should compare CPU and GPU models\predictions,[],[],0,"Following #796 - our tests for GPU supporting models also do not validate that the models provided by CPU and GPU training provide similar predictions (up to some tolerance).

Since the `predict()` function itself may also utilize the GPU - we need to test the full 4-way matrix (trained on CPU\GPU, predicted on CPU\GPU) - and verify that in all 4 cases results remain the same.",{},{}
15203,IssuesEvent,2018-08-14 18:43:35+00:00,112676803,apple/turicreate,5673251,znation,10639145,apple,closed,Test binaries should dynamically link their dependencies,"[{'id': 783171922, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3ODMxNzE5MjI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apple/turicreate/labels/cleanup', 'name': 'cleanup', 'color': '34c92c', 'default': False}, {'id': 977505788, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw5Nzc1MDU3ODg=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apple/turicreate/labels/p3', 'name': 'p3', 'color': '90bcdb', 'default': False}, {'id': 962939852, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw5NjI5Mzk4NTI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apple/turicreate/labels/testing', 'name': 'testing', 'color': 'c1ea62', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Current test binaries come out to 50+ MB, because they are statically linking (some? most? all?) their dependencies. We should be dynamically linking where possible to save on incremental build time, disk space used, etc., especially considering our actual Python package dynamically links the same thing (so it's a better test case to link the same way the Python process will).",{},{}
15211,IssuesEvent,2018-08-14 17:06:05+00:00,112676803,apple/turicreate,7035096,devon-stanley,10639145,apple,opened,Please clarify/update GPU requirements,[],[],0,"I saw that object detection now has GPU support for macOS 10.14+ so I went ahead and upgraded my OS. Unfortunately it seems that the Intel Iris chipset isn't supported for GPU usage, so I can't take advantage of the new GPU support. 

