15212,IssuesEvent,2018-08-22 05:36:37+00:00,112676803,apple/turicreate,1875987,srikris,10639145,apple,closed,Add support for macOS 10.11,"[{'id': 782185156, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3ODIxODUxNTY=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apple/turicreate/labels/feature%20request', 'name': 'feature request', 'color': 'b602f2', 'default': False}, {'id': 962936815, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw5NjI5MzY4MTU=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apple/turicreate/labels/setup', 'name': 'setup', 'color': 'b0f939', 'default': False}]",[],0,"It would be nice if Turi Create could be used on macOS 10.11. Functions that rely on `coremltools` would have to fail gracefully (e.g. `export_coreml`). Currently `coremltools==0.6.3` is a hard dependency, and they do not provide wheels for 10.11.",{},{}
15214,IssuesEvent,2018-03-05 22:31:31+00:00,112676803,apple/turicreate,5673251,znation,10639145,apple,opened,kmeans user guide uses invalid subscript syntax,"[{'id': 775278782, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/apple/turicreate/labels/docs', 'name': 'docs', 'color': 'edb423', 'default': False}]",[],0,"In the [kmeans user guide chapter](https://github.com/apple/turicreate/blob/master/userguide/clustering/kmeans.md), the syntax for accessing properties is incorrect in a few places:

```python
kmeans_model['cluster_info']
kmeans_model['cluster_id']
kmeans_sample['cluster_info']
```

These should instead use dot notation (Python object property syntax):

```python
kmeans_model.cluster_info
kmeans_model.cluster_id
kmeans_sample.cluster_info
```",{},{}
