15235,IssuesEvent,2018-06-12 17:09:43+00:00,103890505,ConsenSys/mythril,6525145,Ramlall,10818037,ConsenSys,opened,Jinja2 Import Error From Fresh Ubuntu Install,[],[],0,"I installed Mythril on my Ubuntu 16.04 Virtual Machine using the instructions found on the [wiki page here](https://github.com/ConsenSys/mythril/wiki/Install-from-Pypi-on-Ubuntu). 

When I tried to do a `myth -x contract.sol` on one of the example contracts, I got an import error.

![mytherr](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6525145/41305368-af95996a-6e40-11e8-910d-19cabaa3605c.png)

I googled around and doing 

`sudo pip3 install --upgrade jinja2`

fixed the error and allowed me to use the myth command to test contracts.

So maybe either:
1. Include that command in the wiki instructions (although this is not the neatest solution).
2. Package that command somewhere  in the mythril install process. (Perhaps in `pip3 install mythril`.)

Just bringing it up since it was giving me problems. I'm not sure if this affects every other fresh install. ",{},{}
