15789,IssuesEvent,2016-09-28 20:13:48+00:00,37496521,nteract/nteract,10944582,jdetle,12401040,nteract,opened,Add a theme with the nteract color scheme.,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nteract/nteract/labels/design', 'name': 'design', 'color': '5319e7'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nteract/nteract/labels/new-contributor-friendly', 'name': 'new-contributor-friendly', 'color': 'bfd4f2'}]",[],0,"Currently we have two default themes, light and dark. As a project for new contributors, it would be nice to have a theme that incorporates the color scheme of nteract's logo into the background and/or cell aesthetic. Changing CSS, although not a programming heavy intensive task, is a good way to get started making contributions after going through the hassle of setting up a developer installation. ",{},{}
15805,IssuesEvent,2018-08-22 13:52:13+00:00,35872414,infoportugal/wagtail-modeltranslation,10087166,DiogoMarques29,12510303,infoportugal,closed,"""lock down"" the slug?","[{'id': 213341751, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwyMTMzNDE3NTE=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/infoportugal/wagtail-modeltranslation/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],1,"Right now if you have a localized page, it's possible to create a new page, assign it an English and a French title, publishing it, and then discovering that your `mywebsite.com/en/about-us` does not commute to `mywebsite.com/fr/about-us` because the `slug [fr]` was automatically set based on the page title, and suddenly all your pages live on completely different URLs and you can't add a simple locale switcher that just does a `window.location` replacement for the language code.

That's often not desirable at all, where the URL should be stable save for the country code, so this would be great to put behind some setting variable like `FORCE_TRANSLATE_SLUGS=False` (defaulting to `True` to keep things backward compatible)

(note, this is not about the use of the `slug url` in templates, it's about the actual URLs that wagtail services based on the slug values stored in the database for a page)",{},{}
