15967,IssuesEvent,2018-04-23 12:31:05+00:00,24117057,pytroll/pyresample,1828519,davidh-ssec,13004956,pytroll,closed,Possibly inefficient array segmenting,"[{'id': 130064900, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/pyresample/labels/Priority-Low', 'name': 'Priority-Low', 'color': 'FFFFFF', 'default': False}, {'id': 130055007, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/pyresample/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 130055011, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/pyresample/labels/wontfix', 'name': 'wontfix', 'color': 'ffffff', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'davidh-ssec', 'id': 1828519, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/1828519?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/davidh-ssec', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/davidh-ssec/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",4,"I was looking through some of the nearest neighbor and kdtree stuff and found this section of code:

https://github.com/pytroll/pyresample/blob/master/pyresample/kd_tree.py#L337

```
    if segments > 1:
    # Iterate through segments
    for i, target_slice in enumerate(geometry._get_slice(segments,
                                                         target_geo_def.shape)):

        # Query on slice of target coordinates
        next_voi, next_ia, next_da = \
            _query_resample_kdtree(resample_kdtree, source_geo_def,
                                   target_geo_def,
                                   radius_of_influence, target_slice,
                                   neighbours=neighbours,
                                   epsilon=epsilon,
                                   reduce_data=reduce_data,
                                   nprocs=nprocs)

        # Build result iteratively
        if i == 0:
            # First iteration
            valid_output_index = next_voi
            index_array = next_ia
            distance_array = next_da
        else:
            valid_output_index = np.append(valid_output_index, next_voi)
            if neighbours > 1:
                index_array = np.row_stack((index_array, next_ia))
                distance_array = np.row_stack((distance_array, next_da))
            else:
                index_array = np.append(index_array, next_ia)
                distance_array = np.append(distance_array, next_da)
```

This code is saving memory by processing the data in chunks, but the end result will be the same size. So it is probably faster to allocate the entire end result arrays and write to the appropriate chunk rather than appending (which reallocates and copies the previous array).
",{},{}
