16094,IssuesEvent,2016-05-06 07:01:46+00:00,31315021,Kinto/kinto,229453,Natim,13413813,Kinto,reopened,Crash on records list endpoint when the collection is empty and readonly is true,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Kinto/kinto/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],3,"When the collection has no record and was never reached, a timestamp is stored.

This does not work if `readonly` is true because the user does not have the permission to insert into the timestamp table.

We should not try to bump the timestamp when `readonly` is true.

See:
* Kinto/kinto#433
* https://github.com/mozilla-services/cliquet/pull/649",{},{}
