16286,IssuesEvent,2018-04-19 13:44:00+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,38524111,kirsitn,14095512,IntelRealSense,opened,RealSense viewer - Save settings fails,[],[],0,"| Required Info                         |                                                                |
|---------------------------------|------------------------------------------- |
| Camera Model                       |  D415                                                      | 
| Firmware Version                   |  05.08.15.00                                            | 
| Operating System & Version |  Linux (Ubuntu 16)                                 | 
| Kernel Version (Linux Only)    |  4.4.38                                                    | 
| Platform                                 |  NVIDIA Jetson TX2                                |
| SDK Version                            |   2.9.1                                                    | 


### Issue Description

I am trying to save my current settings from the RealSense viewer, but it fails nearly every time with the error message ""The profile is unsupported!"".  This happens even if I try to save a standard preset such as ""high density"". The only time I am able to save settings is if I do it right after opening the viewer and with settings chosen from the drop-down menu of presets.  Once I have loaded settings from file, I can no longer save any settings (neither standard settings nor the loaded settings). The camera runs normally with the settings I wish to save, so the error message does not seem to have any connection with the settings themselves.

",{},{}
