17188,IssuesEvent,2016-06-10 15:29:17+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,6157939,skebanga,17565521,pybind,opened,"make test works, but unable to run tests individually",[],[],0,"`make test` passes all tests, but attempting to run them individually fails.

This could well just be a documentation issue - as in, the documentation doesn't have details on how to run individual tests from the command line.

How do I run the tests, individually, from the command line?

**Running the tests automatically via makefiles:**

On linux:
  
    $ cmake .
    $ make -j8
    $ make test

> `100% tests passed, 0 tests failed out of 18`

**Attempting to run a test individually:**

    $ ./example/example1.py
  
> ```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""./example/example1.py"", line 6, in <module>
    from example import Example1
ImportError: No module named example
```

**Attempting to run from within the example directory:**

    $ cd example
    $ ./example1.py

> ```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""./example1.py"", line 6, in <module>
    from example import Example1
ImportError: No module named example
```

**Attempt to find the shared library created during the build process:**

    $ find . -name '*.so'
    ./example/example.cpython-34m.so

**Attempt to link `example.cpython-34m.so` to `example.so`:**

    $ ln -s example/example.cpython-34m.so example.so
    $ ./example/example1.py

> ```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""./example/example1.py"", line 6, in <module>
    from example import Example1
ImportError: ./example.so: undefined symbol: PyInstanceMethod_Type
```

**Attempt to link `example.cpython-34m.so` to `example.so` inside example directory:**

    $ cd example
    $ ln -s example.cpython-34m.so example.so
    $ ./example1.py

>```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""./example1.py"", line 6, in <module>
    from example import Example1
ImportError: /home/steve/src/3rd-party/pybind11/example/example.so: undefined symbol: PyInstanceMethod_Type
```

**Show no unresolved dependencies:**

```
$ ldd example.so
	linux-vdso.so.1 =>  (0x00007ffdfa7e8000)
	libstdc++.so.6 => /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libstdc++.so.6 (0x00007fa6d632c000)
