17452,IssuesEvent,2016-10-05 15:11:40+00:00,19141754,opendatateam/udata,7070530,jphnoel,19330690,opendatateam,closed,Switch from microdata to JSON-LD,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/opendatateam/udata/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],4,"## Context
Today, we embed some metadata with the microdata format, i.e. directly within the DOM. We use these metadata both for internal use (in the JS of the dataset frontend) and for external use (SEO). 

## Detailed Description
When we display the dataset page, we need to parse the DOM to retrieve all the metadata, for the modals, and to be able to check the availibility of the resources with Croquemort. 

Let us consider now a dataset with many resources (typically 300, which is a real use cas, encountered in Luxembourg): it does work, from a functional point of view, but it is much too slow.

## Possible Implementation
With [JSON-LD](https://developers.google.com/schemas/formats/json-ld) we should have much better performance.

Moreover, for W3C and Google, microdata is considered as deprecated, and should be replaced by JSON-LD.

Lastly, using microdata makes the templates verbose and harder to maintain. ",{},{}
