17526,IssuesEvent,2018-02-16 11:50:31+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,1658405,LefterisJP,19666847,raiden-network,closed,Use current block gas limit as transaction gas upper bound,"[{'id': 473091760, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/low_hanging_fruit', 'name': 'low_hanging_fruit', 'color': 'bfd4f2', 'default': False}]",[],3,"## Problem Definition

At the moment in raiden we use the [Morden Gas Limit](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/master/raiden/settings.py#L13) as the gas upper bound of all transactions. That is suboptimal as the gas limit can be changed by the miners and in the mainnet is already at the time of writting quite difference. What's worse if for some reason the block gas limit goes below that no transactions will even work.

## Solution

Make sure that all transactions are provided with the actual block gas limit as the upper bound and the result of estimate Gas as the lower bound.


## Tasklist

- [ ] Use the current block's gas limit as the upper bound of a transaction's gas.
",{},{}
17545,IssuesEvent,2018-08-29 11:38:47+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,1658405,LefterisJP,19666847,raiden-network,closed,UPnP port mapper should not reuse existing mappings,"[{'id': 318426945, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzMTg0MjY5NDU=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 892526764, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw4OTI1MjY3NjQ=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/udp', 'name': 'udp', 'color': '22c932', 'default': False}]",[],3,"## Problem Definition

During tests, we found ourselves in a situation where two LAN-IPs got the same port mapping assigned via upnp. We should make sure to ignore existing port mappings and always request a new one during start up.
",{},{}
