17613,IssuesEvent,2017-03-13 15:00:11+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,Interface for tasks to report more status information (checkpoints),"[{'id': 325435541, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Right now the pulse thread monitors the execution of tasks throughout the lifetime of the task, recording memory and CPU usage. It would be useful to allow tasks to report more information through this method (or other methods). The problem is that tasks are mostly single step job so SoS cannot automatically report steps ,",{},{}
17620,IssuesEvent,2017-02-03 01:13:09+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,Control number of jobs in case of nested workflow.,[],[],0,"Right now `sos_run` observes `-j` option independent of the master process. So running a subworkflow in multi-processing mode essentially does

```
J1
J2
J3 --> sos_run --> J5, J6, J7, J8
J4 
```

It should in theory have a process pool to which master and nested workflows send jobs to.
",{},{}
