17673,IssuesEvent,2017-03-10 16:55:26+00:00,37137879,QCoDeS/Qcodes,2694199,giulioungaretti,20478252,QCoDeS,opened,Config  breaks on upstream updates.,"[{'id': 222346529, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/QCoDeS/Qcodes/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'giulioungaretti', 'id': 2694199, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/2694199?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/giulioungaretti', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/giulioungaretti', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/giulioungaretti/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/giulioungaretti/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/giulioungaretti/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/giulioungaretti/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/giulioungaretti/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/giulioungaretti/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/giulioungaretti/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/giulioungaretti/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/giulioungaretti/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"If a user had a custom config and we update upstream by adding a new field.
Their config value will remove the new field added upstream, thus breaking the import of qcodes!

The other way around is impossible to prevent though. If we remove a field upstream there's no way to delete it locally ,or even to raise a warning , but that's cool because maybe local uncommitted doe depends on it :D  At worst it's a bit of extra noise! ",{},{}
