18040,IssuesEvent,2018-01-30 02:38:30+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,11841981,jshir,22243823,streamlink,opened,Vaughnlive changed IP's to break Streamlink,[],[],0,"This will be a very brief bug report... As of tonight the head vaughnlive.py references IPs which were disconnected by vaughn to thwart streamlinking. I've observed vaughn serving video now from ""66.90.93.44"",""66.90.93.35"" and have personally gotten it to work overwriting the IP's in rtmp_server_map with those two alternating. I would submit the commit but I think some more testing is needed as I only use streamlink with one occasional stream and don't know how far those IPs will get more frequent SL users.

